The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, May 12, 2004 				 Sivakasi shootout spillover
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Chennai, May 11: Violence erupted today in parts of Tamil Nadus Sivakasi Lok Sabha constituency where a state minister and two candidates were injured in clashes during polling yesterday. 																								The violence was triggered by a shootout yesterday, allegedly involving sports minister Inbatamizhan and Opposition MDMK candidate Sippiparai Ravichandran. The clash led to a showdown between DMK-MDMK cadre on the one side and ADMK functionaries on the other.																								An angry mob hurled petrol bombs last night at the house of DMKs Virdhunagar district secretary and former minister Sattur Ramachandran. 																								Three vehicles parked in front of his house were set ablaze. More incidents of arson were reported today at various places.																								An ADMK office and the bike of party district secretary Muthuraman were set ablaze. An attempt was also made to torch a mill belonging to a DMK leader.																								Another gang damaged publicity material at MDMK leader Vaikos office at Sivakasi. Vaiko, who was in jail till recently after being arrested under the anti-terror law, has opted out of the Lok Sabha elections this time. He fielded Ravichandran for the high-profile Sivakasi seat against the ADMKs P. Kannan. 
